{"id":4440,"global_id":"www.unitingnc.org?id=4440","global_id_lineage":["www.unitingnc.org?id=4440"],"author":"25","status":"publish","date":"2018-10-01 16:09:30","date_utc":"2018-10-01 20:09:30","modified":"2018-10-01 16:09:30","modified_utc":"2018-10-01 20:09:30","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/stand-with-us\/october-18-standing-with-jose-in-charlotte-acompanando-a-jose-en-clt-greensboro\/","rest_url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-json\/tribe\/events\/v1\/events\/4440","title":"October 18: Standing with Jos\u00e9 in Charlotte \/ Acompa\u00f1ando a Jos\u00e9 en CLT (Greensboro)","description":"<p>Back in July, DACA recipient Jose was sent a summons by the Forsyth County Sheriff&#8217;s Office. Upon presenting himself to the office as instructed, sheriff&#8217;s deputies showed him to a back room, and said someone wanted to talk to him on the phone: an ICE agent. Within hours he was in ICE custody, and spent 10 days in Stewart Detention Center, even though Forsyth County did not bring any criminal charges against him &#8211; his DACA status remains active. Now, ICE is trying to deport Jose, even as he is speaking out (and still has DACA), and going door-to-door in Winston-Salem to train community members in identifying ICE agents. We won&#8217;t let ICE take Jose from us.<br \/>\nLOCATION &#8211; We&#8217;re meeting at Congregational UCC in Greensboro to carpool to Charlotte. Separate Winston-Salem carpool spot TBA.<\/p>\n<p>EN JULIO, Jose, quien tiene DACA, recibi\u00f3 una citaci\u00f3n del Sheriff del Condado de Forsyth. Al presentarse en la oficina seg\u00fan las instrucciones, los ayudantes del sheriff lo llevaron a un cuarto de atr\u00e1s y le dijeron que alguien quer\u00eda hablar con \u00e9l por tel\u00e9fono: un agente de ICE. En cuesti\u00f3n de horas estuvo bajo la custodia de ICE, y pas\u00f3 10 d\u00edas en el Centro de Detenci\u00f3n Stewart, a pesar de que el condado de Forsyth no present\u00f3 cargos penales contra \u00e9l; su estado de DACA permanece activo. Ahora, ICE est\u00e1 tratando de deportar a Jos\u00e9, incluso mientras \u00e9l se est\u00e1 expresando en voz alta (y todav\u00eda tiene DACA), y yendo de puerta en puerta en Winston-Salem para capacitar a los miembros de la comunidad para identificar a los agentes de ICE. No permitiremos que ICE nos quita a Jose.<br \/>\nUBICACI\u00d3N &#8211; Nos reuniremos en Congregational UCC en Greensboro para compartir el viaje a Charlotte. Punto de encuentro separado en Winston-Salem para ser definido.<\/p>","excerpt":"<a href=\"\" class=\"more-link\" title=\"Read More\">Read More<\/a>","slug":"october-18-standing-with-jose-in-charlotte-acompanando-a-jose-en-clt-greensboro","image":{"url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/42785579_2163176200617691_7699967817231106048_n.jpg","id":4441,"extension":"jpg","width":960,"height":540,"sizes":{"thumbnail":{"width":150,"height":150,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/42785579_2163176200617691_7699967817231106048_n-150x150.jpg"},"medium":{"width":300,"height":169,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/42785579_2163176200617691_7699967817231106048_n-300x169.jpg"},"medium_large":{"width":768,"height":432,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/42785579_2163176200617691_7699967817231106048_n-768x432.jpg"},"home-bottom":{"width":150,"height":150,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/42785579_2163176200617691_7699967817231106048_n-150x150.jpg"},"home-middle":{"width":332,"height":190,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/42785579_2163176200617691_7699967817231106048_n-332x190.jpg"},"home-top":{"width":700,"height":400,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg","url":"https:\/\/www.unitingnc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/10\/42785579_216317620